## Gaps: Stated Goals Not Met

| ID | Severity | Problem | Exact Location | Recovery Note |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| G3 | High | Export HTML/CSS selector mismatch. `sectionHTML()` emits flat structures such as `<section class="hero">`, `<h1>`, and `<div class="kicker">`, while CSS expects nested selectors such as `.hero .wrap`, `.hero-figure`, `.masthead .wrap nav`, `.wordmark`, `.cta-banner .wrap`, and `.colophon .wrap`. | `src/render.tsx:432-438` vs `src/templateEngine.ts:56-145` | Fix first. Either make export HTML match the CSS structure or simplify CSS to match exported HTML. |
| G1 | High | `generateTemplateCSS()` always calls `basicCSS()`, so all 12 templates produce identical visual exports. | `src/templateEngine.ts:7-9` | Pair with L1. Start with per-template CSS variables and small layout differences before attempting a full CSS pipeline. |
| G4 | Medium | No template auto-recommendation. Site industry classification exists and templates declare `bestFor[]`, but there is no bridge between them. | `src/pageClassifier.ts:47-81`; `src/templates.ts` `bestFor[]` fields | Pair with L3. Rank templates and surface top recommendations in the template chooser. |
| G2 | Medium | Template `layoutDNA` design specs are not used by builder or renderer. | `src/templates.ts`; `src/localBuilder.ts`; `src/render.tsx` | Defer until G3/G1 are fixed; then decide whether layoutDNA should drive variables, layout modes, or section ordering. |
| G5 | Low | Crawl queue only seeds from priority paths and nav links; in-content links such as “Read more” or “View project” are not crawled. | `src/scraper.ts:301-302`, `src/scraper.ts:328-338` | Consider after core export flow is reliable. |
| G6 | Low | Exported sites reference remote source images directly; exports break if original images go offline. | `src/render.tsx:459` | Implement image download/cache/resize only if static exports need offline durability. |
| G7 | Low | `renderSectionPreview()` and `sectionHTML()` duplicate the same 12-section switch. Adding a section requires editing both paths. | `src/render.tsx:47-416`; `src/render.tsx:429-530+` | Refactor after CSS/HTML alignment to avoid unifying broken behavior. |

## Opposite Gaps: Capabilities Beyond the Stated Purpose

These are not necessarily bad. They are scope mismatches: either formalize them into the product spec or trim them.

| ID | Capability | Where | Decision Needed |
|---|---|---|---|
| O1 | Full 12-section site generator despite the stated “3-page demo” purpose. | `src/types.ts:66-78`; `src/render.tsx` | Decide whether WebSwap is a three-page demo tool or a fuller static-site generator. |
| O2 | 570-line page classification engine. | `src/pageClassifier.ts` | Keep if richer multi-page outputs are part of the real ambition; otherwise simplify. |
| O3 | Model-assisted blueprint pipeline with gateway routing, retry, and Zod validation. | `server.ts:62-157` | Keep if model-assisted planning is core; otherwise local deterministic generation may be enough. |
| O4 | Large React SPA with animations, charts, and icons. | `src/App.tsx` | Keep if operator dashboard matters; trim if the app should be a simpler funnel. |
| O5 | Workspace persistence with path guards. | `src/workspaces.ts` | Likely useful because server-side exports need persistence. |
| O6 | Metrics dashboard with hardcoded values. | `src/App.tsx`; `src/localBuilder.ts:103-115` | Pair with L7 or remove dashboard metrics until they are truthful. |
| O7 | 182-line production CSS system. | `src/templateEngine.ts:15-182` | Valuable only after G3/G1 make CSS align with export HTML and template choice. |

